#compdef picocrypt
# Documentation: https://github.com/Picocrypt/CLI
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-20
# Verified: upstream Picocrypt/CLI README. The CLI accepts only four
# single-letter flags: -p, -r (encryption); -f, -k (decryption). No
# long-form variants exist upstream; mode is auto-detected from input.

# Zsh completion for picocrypt CLI (https://github.com/Picocrypt/CLI)

_arguments -s -S \
  '-p[(encryption) use paranoid mode]' \
  '-r[(encryption) encode with Reed-Solomon]' \
  '-f[(decryption) attempt to fix corruption]' \
  '-k[(decryption) keep output even if corrupted]' \
  '*:file:_files' && return 0
